evidence.text: Plaintiffs filed a motion for a temporary restraining order, ECF No. 8, that was converted to a motion for a preliminary injunction by stipulation of the parties, ECF No. 17. Defendants filed a response in opposition to the motion, ECF No. 29, and Plaintiffs filed a reply in support of it, ECF No. 30.
Upon receipt and review of this supplemental material, the Court provided a deadline for Defendants to respond and ordered that the stipulated restraining order be extended to March 14, 2025.
